com.avaya.csta.binding

Class EndpointRegisteredEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.EndpointRegisteredEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class EndpointRegisteredEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Event object for an endpoint being registered. This event occurs when the endpoint registers (for whatever reason).

    The device parameter that specifies the device that is registered is of type SubjectDeviceID so extracting the device ID is a two-step process: 

      SubjectDeviceID subjDeviceID = event.getDevice();
  DeviceID deviceID = subjDeviceID.getDeviceIdentifier();
